.TH "klp_get_state" 9 "klp_get_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
klp_get_state \- get information about system state modified by the given patch
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct klp_state *" klp_get_state
.BI "(struct klp_patch *patch "  ","
.BI "unsigned long id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "patch" 12
livepatch that modifies the given system state
.IP "id" 12
custom identifier of the modified system state
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks whether the given patch modifies the given system state.

The function can be called either from pre/post (un)patch
callbacks or from the kernel code added by the livepatch.
.SH "RETURN"
pointer to struct klp_state when found, otherwise NULL.
